No Case of Blood Coagulation Disorder in Africa. The World Health Organization has said that there are still rising cases of covid-19 in 15 African Countries including Kenya, Ethiopia, Libya and Tunisia.  During the WHO Africa Online Briefing today, Vaccine Preventable Disease Program Coordinator for WHO Region Office for Africa Dr. Richard Mihigo who made the revelation noted that currently, 45 countries have so far vaccinated their citizens.  While noting that Africa's monitoring and reporting systems are working well, Dr. Mihigo further states that all African countries have baseline safety surveillance systems in place which helps in reporting any side effects that may be recorded following vaccination.